---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" path="/privacy/" description="Privacy Policy for NEXOR SIGNAL.">
  <section class="container page-hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">Privacy</div>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>NEXOR SIGNAL is designed to collect as little personal data as possible.</p>
  </section>

  <article class="container article">
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 25, 2026</p>

    <p>
      NEXOR SIGNAL is an independent website covering AI, systems, markets, and compute culture.
      This Privacy Policy explains what information may be collected when you visit the site,
      subscribe, contact us, or support the project.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Who controls this website</h2>
    <p>
      The controller for this website is <strong>NEXOR SIGNAL</strong>.
      You can contact us at:
      <a href="mailto:hello@nexorsignal.com">hello@nexorsignal.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
    <p>
      We aim to keep data collection minimal. Depending on how you use the site, we may process:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Email address</strong> — if you subscribe to updates or contact us.</li>
      <li><strong>Message content</strong> — if you send us an email or contact request.</li>
      <li><strong>Basic technical data</strong> — such as IP address, browser type, device information, request URLs, timestamps, and server logs generated by our hosting provider for security and reliability.</li>
      <li><strong>Support-related data</strong> — if you support NEXOR SIGNAL through Buy Me a Coffee, Bitcoin / Lightning, or another external payment method.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How we use information</h2>
    <p>We use information only for clear and limited purposes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>to send updates if you subscribe;</li>
      <li>to reply when you contact us;</li>
      <li>to keep the website secure and reliable;</li>
      <li>to understand whether the site is functioning correctly;</li>
      <li>to process or acknowledge support, tips, or contributions where applicable.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Legal basis</h2>
    <p>
      If you are in the European Economic Area or the United Kingdom, we process personal data under the following legal bases:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Consent</strong> — when you subscribe to updates or choose to contact us.</li>
      <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> — to operate, secure, maintain, and improve the website.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> — if we are required to keep certain information for compliance, accounting, or legal reasons.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Newsletter and email</h2>
    <p>
      If you subscribe, we use your email address to send NEXOR SIGNAL updates.
      You can unsubscribe or ask to be removed at any time by contacting
      <a href="mailto:hello@nexorsignal.com">hello@nexorsignal.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Payments and support</h2>
    <p>
      NEXOR SIGNAL may link to external support services such as Buy Me a Coffee or Bitcoin / Lightning wallet tools.
      These services are operated by third parties and may process your data under their own privacy policies.
      We do not receive or store your full payment card details.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Cookies and tracking</h2>
    <p>
      NEXOR SIGNAL does not intentionally use invasive advertising trackers.
      The site is designed to work without requiring visitor accounts or a heavy tracking stack.
      If analytics, embedded media, newsletter tools, or payment tools are added later,
      this policy should be updated to describe those services clearly.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Hosting and server logs</h2>
    <p>
      The website is hosted by third-party infrastructure providers.
      Like most websites, hosting providers may automatically process basic technical data,
      including IP addresses, timestamps, browser information, request URLs, and error logs.
      This is used for security, debugging, uptime, abuse prevention, and service reliability.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Data retention</h2>
    <p>We keep personal data only as long as needed for the purpose it was collected:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>newsletter email addresses are kept until you unsubscribe or ask to be removed;</li>
      <li>contact emails may be kept for up to 12 months unless a longer period is needed for legitimate or legal reasons;</li>
      <li>server logs are retained according to the hosting provider’s operational and security practices;</li>
      <li>support or payment records may be retained by the relevant third-party provider according to their own policies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>10. Sharing data</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell personal data.
      We may share limited information only with service providers needed to operate the site,
      deliver email, process support, host the website, prevent abuse, or comply with legal obligations.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your location, you may have the right to access, correct, delete, restrict, or object to the processing of your personal data.
      You may also have the right to withdraw consent and request a copy of your data.
    </p>
    <p>
      To exercise these rights, contact:
      <a href="mailto:hello@nexorsignal.com">hello@nexorsignal.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>12. External links</h2>
    <p>
      NEXOR SIGNAL may link to external websites, platforms, tools, payment providers, or social media pages.
      We are not responsible for the privacy practices of external websites.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy as the site evolves.
      The latest version will always be published on this page.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy can be sent to:
      <a href="mailto:hello@nexorsignal.com">hello@nexorsignal.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
